text: Owen Williams (20 June 1847 - 18 November 1917) was an Australian cricketer. He played four first-class cricket matches for Victoria between 1871 and 1876. Williams was a cricket writer for The Australasian under the pen name "Tom Brown". ==See also== * List of Victoria first-class cricketers ==References== ==External links== * Category:1847 births Category:1917 deaths Category:Australian cricketers Category:Victoria cricketers
title: Owen Williams (Australian cricketer)
